.Dd 2026-07-21
.Dt BIDLE 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm bidle
.Nd run a program after a period of X inactivity
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl t Ar timeout
.Op Fl p Ar program
.Op Fl i Ar interval
.Op Fl nv
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
watches the X server for user inactivity and runs
.Ar program
once the keyboard and pointer have been idle for at least
.Ar timeout
seconds.
It is a portable replacement for
.Xr xidle 1 ,
which depends on the OpenBSD-specific XIDLE extension:
.Nm
queries the MIT-SCREEN-SAVER extension for the idle time \(em the same approach
taken by
.Xr xautolock 1
\(em which is available on
.Ox ,
.Fx ,
and Linux alike.
.Pp
Every
.Ar interval
seconds
.Nm
polls the idle time and, the first time it meets the threshold within an idle
episode, forks
.Ar program
into its own session.
Only one invocation is issued per episode: a subsequent run is suppressed until
activity is observed again, so a program that exits immediately
.Pq e.g.\& a misconfigured locker
does not cause a respawn storm.
The child is detached via
.Xr setsid 2
and reaped automatically
.Pq Dv SIGCHLD No is set to Dv SIG_IGN ,
so
.Nm
never blocks waiting for it.
.Pp
.Nm
runs until killed by a signal or the display connection is lost.
.Pp
On
.Ox ,
.Nm
calls
.Xr pledge 2
with
.Qq stdio rpath proc exec
after opening the display.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl t Ar timeout
Idle threshold in seconds before
.Ar program
is launched.
Defaults to 300 (5 minutes).
.It Fl p Ar program
Program to run, located via
.Ev PATH
with
.Xr execlp 3 .
Defaults to
.Xr slock 1 .
.It Fl i Ar interval
Seconds between idle-time polls.
Defaults to 1.
.It Fl n
Dry-run: print the would-be command to stderr instead of forking.
Implies no child is ever spawned.
.It Fl v
Verbose: log the configured values and, on each poll, the current idle time
to stderr.
.El
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width "DISPLAY" -compact
.It Ev DISPLAY
X server to connect to.
.It Ev PATH
Used to locate
.Ar program .
.El
.Sh SIGNALS
.Bl -tag -width "SIGCHLD" -compact
.It Dv SIGINT , Dv SIGTERM
Close the display and exit cleanly.
.It Dv SIGCHLD
Set to
.Dv SIG_IGN
so spawned children are reaped without blocking the poll loop.
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Sh EXAMPLES
Lock the screen after 5 minutes of inactivity, started from the session:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
bidle &
.Ed
.Pp
Run a custom locker after 10 minutes, polling every 5 seconds:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
bidle -t 600 -p xlock -i 5 &
.Ed
.Pp
Inspect the idle reporting without launching anything:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ bidle -n -t 1 -v
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr slock 1 ,
.Xr xidle 1 ,
.Xr xautolock 1 ,
.Xr Xss 3 ,
.Xr pledge 2
.Sh BUGS
The idle time is server-wide \(em time since the last input event anywhere on
the display \(em and not per-window.
.Pp
A program that injects synthetic input events
.Pq e.g.\& Xr xdotool 1
resets the idle counter and so can prevent the timeout from ever firing; this
is inherent to any idle-based locker.
